refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
arraypg_fetch_all PgSql\Resultresult intmodePGSQL_ASSOC
pg_fetch_all returns an array that contains all rows (records) in the PgSql\Result instance.
&database.fetch-null;

&reftitle.parameters;
result
&pgsql.parameter.result;
mode
An optional parameter that controls how the returned array is indexed. mode is a constant and can take the following values: PGSQL_ASSOC, PGSQL_NUM and PGSQL_BOTH. Using PGSQL_NUM, pg_fetch_all will return an array with numerical indices, using PGSQL_ASSOC it will return only associative indices while PGSQL_BOTH will return both numerical and associative indices.

&reftitle.returnvalues;


 An array with all rows in the result.  Each row is an array
 of field values indexed by field name.

&reftitle.changelog;







     &Version;
     &Description;



    &pgsql.changelog.result-object;


     8.0.0

      pg_fetch_all will now return an empty &array;
      instead of &false; for result sets with zero rows.




     7.1.0

      The mode parameter was added.

  &reftitle.examples;



    PostgreSQL fetch all


<?php 
$conn = pg_pconnect("dbname=publisher");
if (!$conn) {
    echo "An error occurred.\n";
    exit;
}

$result = pg_query($conn, "SELECT * FROM authors");
if (!$result) {
    echo "An error occurred.\n";
    exit;
}

$arr = pg_fetch_all($result);

print_r($arr);

?>


